---
import { Image } from 'astro:assets';
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import PageHero from '../components/PageHero.astro';
import CTASection from '../components/CTASection.astro';
import { site } from '../data/site';
import meetingTable from '../assets/images/meeting-table.jpg';

const personSchema = {
  '@context': 'https://schema.org',
  '@type': 'Person',
  name: site.founder,
  jobTitle: 'Independent AI Consultant',
  worksFor: { '@id': `${site.url}/#business` },
  knowsAbout: [
    'Product management',
    'Enterprise SaaS',
    'AI implementation',
    'Workflow automation',
    'Cyber security awareness',
    'AWS',
  ],
  address: { '@type': 'PostalAddress', addressLocality: 'Manchester', addressCountry: 'GB' },
};
---

<Base
  title="About - Why AIisCurious Exists | AIisCurious"
  description="AIisCurious is one experienced product leader helping small businesses across the North West adopt AI with confidence. No agency, no jargon, practical help from a real person."
  schema={[personSchema]}
>
  <PageHero
    eyebrow="About"
    title="Hello, I’m James."
    lede="I help small businesses take their first confident step into AI. Not with strategy decks or buzzwords, with plain English, practical setups and honest advice about what’s worth doing."
    crumbs={[{ label: 'About' }]}
  />

  <section class="section--sm">
    <div class="container container--narrow">
      <Image
        src={meetingTable}
        alt="People talking around a sunlit wooden table with notebooks, mid-conversation"
        widths={[640, 1000, 1400]}
        sizes="(min-width: 800px) 46rem, 92vw"
        class="about-photo"
      />
      <div class="prose">
        <h2>Why AIisCurious exists</h2>
        <p>
          A couple of years ago I started noticing the same conversation happening everywhere,
          at family gatherings, in pubs, with friends who run trades businesses and shops and small
          practices. It went like this: <em>“I know we should be doing something with this AI stuff.
          I just don’t know what, and I don’t know who to ask.”</em>
        </p>
        <p>
          The people asking weren’t behind. They were busy, running real businesses, looking after
          customers and staff, without a spare afternoon to test tools or decode breathless AI
          headlines. And the help on offer was all wrong for them: expensive consultancies built for
          corporates, agencies selling whatever earns commission, and an internet full of hype
          written for Silicon Valley rather than a twelve-person firm in Stockport.
        </p>
        <p>
          AIisCurious exists to be the missing option: <strong>one experienced person who’ll look
          at your business, tell you honestly where AI helps (and where it doesn’t), and set it up
          properly if you want the help.</strong>
        </p>

        <h2>The background I bring</h2>
        <p>
          I’ve spent my career in product management and enterprise software, the job of standing
          between complicated technology and the people who need it to just work. That’s included
          implementing AI systems in production, building automation that teams rely on daily,
          working with AWS and modern cloud tooling, and, importantly for this work, a strong
          grounding in cyber security awareness.
        </p>
        <p>
          That last part matters more than people expect. The biggest genuine risk for a small
          business adopting AI isn’t choosing the wrong tool, it’s putting customer data somewhere
          it shouldn’t go. Every piece of work I do starts with getting that right.
        </p>

        <h2>How I work</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Plain English, always.</strong> If I can’t explain it simply, I don’t understand it well enough, and you shouldn’t pay for it.</li>
          <li><strong>Fixed prices.</strong> Scoped and agreed up front. No day rates, no meters running.</li>
          <li><strong>Honesty over sales.</strong> If AI isn’t worth it for your business yet, your free report will say exactly that.</li>
          <li><strong>Independence.</strong> I don’t resell tools or take commissions. Recommendations are based on what fits you.</li>
          <li><strong>You own everything.</strong> Accounts, automations, documentation, all yours, all handed over. Nothing is designed to make you dependent on me.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Why “curious”?</h2>
        <p>
          Because that’s the honest starting point, for you and for me. Nobody has AI fully figured
          out, and anyone who claims to is selling something. What works is curiosity applied
          practically: try the small thing, measure whether it helped, keep what works, drop what
          doesn’t. That mindset, more than any tool, is what I try to leave behind in every business
          I work with.
        </p>
        <p>
          If you’re curious too, the first conversation is free, and it’s a conversation, not a
          pitch.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <CTASection
    heading="Let’s have that first conversation"
    text="Fifteen minutes about your business. A personalised report within three days. And an honest answer about whether AI is worth your time right now."
  />
</Base>

<style>
  :global(.about-photo) {
    width: 100%;
    height: auto;
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
    box-shadow: var(--shadow);
    margin-bottom: clamp(2rem, 1.5rem + 2vw, 3rem);
  }
</style>
